message.text:
𝑴𝑻𝒂𝒎𝒑𝒍𝒊𝒇𝒚 : 𝐅𝐨𝐫𝐞𝐟𝐫𝐨𝐧𝐭 𝐨𝐟 𝐑𝐞𝐩𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐄𝐦𝐩𝐨𝐰𝐞𝐫𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭

 In its commitment to uplift every student’s voice, the Medical Technology Society proudly unveils 𝐌𝐓𝐚𝐦𝐩𝐥𝐢𝐟𝐲, a platform designed to amplify concerns, foster inclusivity, and ensure that no student goes unheard. 

 This is an initiative to extend the reach of the 𝗦𝗼𝗰𝗶𝗼-𝗖𝗶𝘃𝗶𝗰 𝗗𝗲𝗽𝗮𝗿𝘁𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 by establishing three subcommittees dedicated to foster a more inclusive environment where each subcommittees are representing particular sectors of the Medtech Community:

- Student Scholars Committee
- Irregular Students Committee
- SWAN (Students With Additional Needs) Committee

In line with this, MTamplify strives to embrace diversity, creates a system where students can freely voice out concerns, and provide a formal mechanism for dialogue between student groups, MTSoc, and the administration. Above all, it seeks continuous improvement of the student’s experience by giving voices to those underrepresented communities, making sure that no one is left behind.
 
𝗠𝗲𝗺𝗯𝗲𝗿𝘀𝗵𝗶𝗽 𝗣𝗿𝗶𝗺𝗲𝗿:
🔗 https://docs.google.com/document/d/1aFPtxsJdssuwLQaNF87xA631jZR6NZ5QVgmbsGOzk_s/edit?usp=drivesdk 

𝗗𝗲𝗮𝗱𝗹𝗶𝗻𝗲 𝗼𝗳 𝗠𝗲𝗺𝗯𝗲𝗿𝘀𝗵𝗶𝗽: 𝑺𝒆𝒑𝒕𝒆𝒎𝒃𝒆𝒓 𝟐𝟒, 𝟐𝟎𝟐𝟓
𝗠𝗲𝗺𝗯𝗲𝗿𝘀𝗵𝗶𝗽 𝗟𝗶𝗻𝗸:
🔗 https://forms.office.com
🔗 https://forms.office.com
🔗 https://forms.office.com

Giving every student a platform, MTamplify unleashes the power to be timeless, ensuring that today’s voices shape tomorrow’s legacy. 

#PoweredToBeTimeless
#XIIMTSoc
#FEUMTS

Caption by Kiara Capistrano 
Publication Material by Erika Longatang

message.text:
𝑴𝑻𝒂𝒎𝒑𝒍𝒊𝒇𝒚 : 𝐅𝐨𝐫𝐞𝐟𝐫𝐨𝐧𝐭 𝐨𝐟 𝐑𝐞𝐩𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐄𝐦𝐩𝐨𝐰𝐞𝐫𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭

 In its commitment to uplift every student’s voice, the Medical Technology Society proudly unveils 𝐌𝐓𝐚𝐦𝐩𝐥𝐢𝐟𝐲, a platform designed to amplify concerns, foster inclusivity, and ensure that no student goes unheard. 

 This is an initiative to extend the reach of the 𝗦𝗼𝗰𝗶𝗼-𝗖𝗶𝘃𝗶𝗰 𝗗𝗲𝗽𝗮𝗿𝘁𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 by establishing three subcommittees dedicated to foster a more inclusive environment where each subcommittees are representing particular sectors of the Medtech Community:

- Student Scholars Committee
- Irregular Students Committee
- SWAN (Students With Additional Needs) Committee

In line with this, MTamplify strives to embrace diversity, creates a system where students can freely voice out concerns, and provide a formal mechanism for dialogue between student groups, MTSoc, and the administration. Above all, it seeks continuous improvement of the student’s experience by giving voices to those underrepresented communities, making sure that no one is left behind.
 
𝗠𝗲𝗺𝗯𝗲𝗿𝘀𝗵𝗶𝗽 𝗣𝗿𝗶𝗺𝗲𝗿:
🔗 https://docs.google.com/document/d/1aFPtxsJdssuwLQaNF87xA631jZR6NZ5QVgmbsGOzk_s/edit?usp=drivesdk 

𝗗𝗲𝗮𝗱𝗹𝗶𝗻𝗲 𝗼𝗳 𝗠𝗲𝗺𝗯𝗲𝗿𝘀𝗵𝗶𝗽: 𝑺𝒆𝒑𝒕𝒆𝒎𝒃𝒆𝒓 𝟐𝟒, 𝟐𝟎𝟐𝟓
𝗠𝗲𝗺𝗯𝗲𝗿𝘀𝗵𝗶𝗽 𝗟𝗶𝗻𝗸:
🔗 https://forms.office.com
🔗 https://forms.office.com
🔗 https://forms.office.com

Giving every student a platform, MTamplify unleashes the power to be timeless, ensuring that today’s voices shape tomorrow’s legacy. 

#PoweredToBeTimeless
#XIIMTSoc
#FEUMTS

Caption by Kiara Capistrano 
Publication Material by Erika Longatang

Publication Material by Erika Longatang

𝑴𝑻𝒂𝒎𝒑𝒍𝒊𝒇𝒚 : 𝐅𝐨𝐫𝐞𝐟𝐫𝐨𝐧𝐭 𝐨𝐟 𝐑𝐞𝐩𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐄𝐦𝐩𝐨𝐰𝐞𝐫𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭

 In its commitment to uplift every student’s voice, the Medical Technology Society proudly unveils 𝐌𝐓𝐚𝐦𝐩𝐥𝐢𝐟𝐲, a platform designed to amplify concerns, foster inclusivity, and ensure that no student goes unheard. 

 This is an initiative to extend the reach of the 𝗦𝗼𝗰𝗶𝗼-𝗖𝗶𝘃𝗶𝗰 𝗗𝗲𝗽𝗮𝗿𝘁𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 by establishing three subcommittees dedicated to foster a more inclusive environment where each subcommittees are representing particular sectors of the Medtech Community:

- Student Scholars Committee
- Irregular Students Committee
- SWAN (Students With Additional Needs) Committee

In line with this, MTamplify strives to embrace diversity, creates a system where students can freely voice out concerns, and provide a formal mechanism for dialogue between student groups, MTSoc, and the administration. Above all, it seeks continuous improvement of the student’s experience by giving voices to those underrepresented communities, making sure that no one is left behind.

message.text:
𝑴𝑻𝒂𝒎𝒑𝒍𝒊𝒇𝒚 : 𝐅𝐨𝐫𝐞𝐟𝐫𝐨𝐧𝐭 𝐨𝐟 𝐑𝐞𝐩𝐫𝐞𝐬𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐄𝐦𝐩𝐨𝐰𝐞𝐫𝐦𝐞𝐧𝐭

 In its commitment to uplift every student’s voice, the Medical Technology Society proudly unveils 𝐌𝐓𝐚𝐦𝐩𝐥𝐢𝐟𝐲, a platform designed to amplify concerns, foster inclusivity, and ensure that no student goes unheard. 

 This is an initiative to extend the reach of the 𝗦𝗼𝗰𝗶𝗼-𝗖𝗶𝘃𝗶𝗰 𝗗𝗲𝗽𝗮𝗿𝘁𝗺𝗲𝗻𝘁 by establishing three subcommittees dedicated to foster a more inclusive environment where each subcommittees are representing particular sectors of the Medtech Community:

- Student Scholars Committee
- Irregular Students Committee
- SWAN (Students With Additional Needs) Committee

In line with this, MTamplify strives to embrace diversity, creates a system where students can freely voice out concerns, and provide a formal mechanism for dialogue between student groups, MTSoc, and the administration. Above all, it seeks continuous improvement of the student’s experience by giving voices to those underrepresented communities, making sure that no one is left behind.
 
𝗠𝗲𝗺𝗯𝗲𝗿𝘀𝗵𝗶𝗽 𝗣𝗿𝗶𝗺𝗲𝗿:
🔗 https://docs.google.com/document/d/1aFPtxsJdssuwLQaNF87xA631jZR6NZ5QVgmbsGOzk_s/edit?usp=drivesdk 

𝗗𝗲𝗮𝗱𝗹𝗶𝗻𝗲 𝗼𝗳 𝗠𝗲𝗺𝗯𝗲𝗿𝘀𝗵𝗶𝗽: 𝑺𝒆𝒑𝒕𝒆𝒎𝒃𝒆𝒓 𝟐𝟒, 𝟐𝟎𝟐𝟓
𝗠𝗲𝗺𝗯𝗲𝗿𝘀𝗵𝗶𝗽 𝗟𝗶𝗻𝗸:
🔗 https://forms.office.com
🔗 https://forms.office.com
🔗 https://forms.office.com

Giving every student a platform, MTamplify unleashes the power to be timeless, ensuring that today’s voices shape tomorrow’s legacy. 

#PoweredToBeTimeless
#XIIMTSoc
#FEUMTS

Caption by Kiara Capistrano 
Publication Material by Erika Longatang
